Logic.Boards

Class Square

  • java.lang.Object
    • Logic.Boards.Square

  • public class Square
extends java.lang.Object
    The Square class a ChessBoard object is constructed from.

    In the Square object we will keep track of what kind of game piece, if any, is placed on the square. The position of Square will be stored in a Coordinate object.

    See Also:
    ChessBoard, Coordinate, GamePieces

      • Square

        public Square(javafx.scene.paint.Color color,
              double width,
              double height,
              int xCoordinate,
              int yCoordinate)
        Creates a Square object for the Chessboard. Note that the (0,0) coordinate will be the the top left corner.
        Parameters:
        color - The color the Square will be displayed with.
        width - The width in pixels.
        height - The height in pixels
        xCoordinate - the x coordinate the square will be on the Chessboard
        yCoordinate - the y coordinate the square will on the Chessboard
